The challenge going forward will be to ensure that the vaccines are produced and distributed for administration, one would think. However, there are also emerging the realisation that the enthusiasm and elation over the vaccines is not a shared one.
There are persons worldwide who do not believe in and have flatly declared that they would not take the vaccine even if the vaccine were to be made available at no cost.



