There is the thinking in some countries that the taking of the vaccines should be made legally mandatory owing to the overall public health challenge that the Covid-19 pandemic poses to the world. The opponents to vaccines cite many reasons and excuses as to efficacy and safety.
However, a number of them argue that administration of vaccines would not only offend their religious rights but also constitute invasion of their privacy and their respective rights to personal autonomy.
Obtaining a visa
This leaves open the question whether a law can mandate the taking of vaccinations and or any time of medication as a compulsory public health requirement. For purposes of international travel, some countries do mandate some vaccination as a condition for obtaining a visa or for gaining entry to their territories.



