The judges held that the patient was entitled to refuse blood transfusion because human dignity is inviolable and that other values are instrumental compared to respect for persons. In another case, a patient was hospitalised in a critical condition while unconscious. He had previously signed a written oath where he declared his wish not to receive blood transfusions even under risk of death.



